about.summary: An extension to shiny that brings interactions and animation effects from 'jQuery UI' library.

name: r-shinyjqui
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.3.3' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-shinyjqui
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/shinyjqui_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/shinyjqui/shinyjqui_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3d218466c161a3b155ce061b5b5912a12cd4de077df3ae336fa6a33b6b979158

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-htmltools
    - r-htmlwidgets
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-shiny >=0.14.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-htmltools
    - r-htmlwidgets
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-shiny >=0.14.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('shinyjqui')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('shinyjqui')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/yang-tang/shinyjqui
  license: MIT
  summary: An extension to shiny that brings interactions and animation effects from 'jQuery
    UI' library.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
